Requirements Authority:
- When requirements conflict, use this order: SRS > FYP1 > STD.
- `docs/PROJECT_SPEC.md` is the operational single source of truth for consolidated requirements.

Design System:
- Visual theme: dark-first dashboard UI.
- Primary colors:
  - Background: #0a0a0a / #0f0f0f
  - Surface: #1e1e1e
  - Border: #262626 / #321315
  - Primary accent: #c0392b / #8B0000 / #df1f25
  - Text primary: #ffffff / #f4f5f7
  - Text muted: #9aa0ad / gray-300/400
- Typography:
  - Sans: Inter
  - Display: Space Grotesk
  - Monospace: JetBrains Mono
- Layout:
  - Fixed left sidebar navigation by role
  - Main content cards with rounded corners and strong contrast
  - Consistent spacing and hierarchy for forms/tables/charts

User Roles and Permissions:
- Admin:
  - Full dashboard access
  - Manage users and role assignments
  - Access invoices, payments, reports, settings, permissions matrix
- Accountant:
  - Access dashboard, invoices, payments, reports
  - Record payments, generate invoices/reports, trigger reminders
  - No user/permission administration
- Sales Staff:
  - Access sales dashboard, invoices (read status), clients, and sale recording
  - No access to payments/reports/user administration

Accessibility and Contrast Rule (strict):
- Never use dark text on dark backgrounds.
- Ensure all text/background combinations meet readable contrast (target WCAG AA minimum).
- Validate focus states, hover states, and placeholder visibility on dark surfaces.
- If uncertain, prefer lighter text tokens on dark UI components.

Implementation Guardrails:
- Do not silently change requirement behavior without updating `docs/PROJECT_SPEC.md`.
- For each feature change, reference FR/UC/TC IDs in comments, PR notes, or commit notes.
- Keep route/middleware access consistent with role permissions above.
- Preserve auditability for financial and configuration actions.
